---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Dataset - Instrumetriq"
  description="Dataset notes for normalized public X (Twitter) post records and windowed summaries."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="DATASET"
    title="Dataset"
    subtitle="Validated market snapshots combining price microstructure, spot sampling, and frozen social sentiment windows."
  />
  <div class="pageContent">
    <section>
      <h2>About the Dataset</h2>
      <p>
        A record is a single validated <strong>v7 snapshot</strong>—frozen at admission and required to pass dataset health gates (700+ spot samples minimum). Each snapshot captures a moment in time, combining market microstructure, high-resolution price samples, and aggregated social sentiment windows.
      </p>
      <p>
        See <a href="/status">Status</a> for current validated record counts.
      </p>
    </section>
    
    <section>
      <h2>What is a Snapshot?</h2>
      <p>
        Each snapshot is a structured observation of a single cryptocurrency symbol at a specific moment. A single record contains:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Symbol:</strong> The cryptocurrency being observed (e.g., BTC, AAVE, ETH)</li>
        <li><strong>Timestamp:</strong> UTC timestamp marking when the snapshot was captured</li>
        <li><strong>Spot price microstructure:</strong> Bid/ask spreads, order book depth, liquidity metrics</li>
        <li><strong>700+ spot price samples:</strong> High-resolution price observations collected over a fixed window</li>
        <li><strong>Social sentiment windows:</strong> Aggregated, frozen sentiment metrics from X (Twitter)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>Important:</strong> This is <em>not</em> a live feed. Each snapshot is a frozen observation, validated and archived for research use.
      </p>
    </section>
    
    <section>
      <h2>Snapshot Anatomy</h2>
      <p>
        Each snapshot is organized into conceptual blocks. This is a high-level view—detailed schema documentation will accompany public releases.
      </p>
      <div class="anatomy-grid">
        <div class="anatomy-block">
          <h3>spot_raw</h3>
          <p>Market microstructure & liquidity context. Includes bid/ask spreads, order book snapshots, and exchange-level metadata.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="anatomy-block">
          <h3>spot_prices</h3>
          <p>High-resolution price samples collected over a fixed window. Provides fine-grained visibility into price movement and volatility.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="anatomy-block">
          <h3>twitter_sentiment_windows</h3>
          <p>Aggregated social sentiment metrics from X (Twitter). Windows are frozen at snapshot time and provide context on public narrative activity.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="anatomy-block">
          <h3>scores / flags</h3>
          <p>Derived context and quality markers. Includes validation results, admission criteria, and computed indicators.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <section>
      <h2>Data Validation & Quality Gates</h2>
      <p>
        Only validated entries appear in public counts. Every snapshot must meet strict quality requirements:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>v7 schema only:</strong> All snapshots conform to the v7 data model</li>
        <li><strong>Type checking:</strong> Required blocks must exist and have correct structure</li>
        <li><strong>700+ spot samples minimum:</strong> Insufficient sampling results in exclusion</li>
        <li><strong>Health gates:</strong> Automated checks verify data completeness and integrity</li>
        <li><strong>Repeatability:</strong> All validation is automated and deterministic</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Entries that fail quality gates are excluded from public counts. <strong>This page reflects only validated entries.</strong>
      </p>
    </section>
    
    <section>
      <h2>What this dataset is — and isn't</h2>
      <div class="is-isnt-grid">
        <div class="is-block">
          <h3>Is</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>A research-grade market observability dataset</li>
            <li>Suitable for analysis, filtering, conditioning, and academic research</li>
            <li>Validated, structured, and reproducible</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="isnt-block">
          <h3>Is not</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>A trading signal or prediction engine</li>
            <li>A guarantee of price movement or correlation</li>
            <li>Financial advice or investment guidance</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <section>
      <h2>Dataset Structure</h2>
      <p>
        Detailed schema documentation, file formats, and field definitions will be provided with the first public release. Future documentation will include versioned schemas, migration guides, and format specifications.
      </p>
    </section>
    
    <section>
      <h2>Access & Licensing</h2>
      <p>
        Public releases will include comprehensive documentation and a Python quickstart for reading and exploring the data. Access terms and licensing details will be finalized and published alongside the first release.
      </p>
    </section>
    
    <section>
      <h2>Citation</h2>
      <p>
        If you use this dataset in your research, please cite it appropriately. Citation guidelines and version-specific references will be provided with versioned releases.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .anatomy-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }
  
  .anatomy-block {
    padding: var(--space-4);
    background-color: var(--panel2);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-dim);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  
  .anatomy-block h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
  }
  
  .anatomy-block p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  
  .is-isnt-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }
  
  .is-block, .isnt-block {
    padding: var(--space-4);
    background-color: var(--panel2);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  
  .is-block {
    border-left: 3px solid #10b981;
  }
  
  .isnt-block {
    border-left: 3px solid #ef4444;
  }
  
  .is-block h3, .isnt-block h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  
  .is-block ul, .isnt-block ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
  }
  
  .is-block li, .isnt-block li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
</style>
